WEBVTT

00:01.523 --> 00:03.177
Previously on "Claws"...

00:03.220 --> 00:04.308
"I would like to bequeath
the remainder

00:04.352 --> 00:06.658
of my fortune
to Polly Marks."

00:06.702 --> 00:09.400
So let's have
a baby together.

00:09.444 --> 00:11.837
Yes.
Yeah.

00:11.881 --> 00:13.578
Baylor, you remember EJ.

00:13.622 --> 00:16.059
You guys can stay
with Black Daddy.

00:16.103 --> 00:18.018
-Okay.
-Okay.

00:18.061 --> 00:22.935
You filthy betraying bitch,
get the hell out!

00:22.979 --> 00:25.025
I think Georgia's been stealing
our pills and selling them.

00:25.068 --> 00:28.332
You know loyalty doesn't just
mean bringing me a problem.

00:28.376 --> 00:30.160
You brought that little bitch
in here,

00:30.204 --> 00:31.944
and you got to see her out.

00:31.988 --> 00:34.730
You know what your problem is?Well, you gonna tell me!

00:34.773 --> 00:38.038
You will never succeed,
Jennifer, being soft!

00:38.081 --> 00:40.910
You want to be
everybody's friend?

00:40.953 --> 00:42.564
[ Gunshots ]

00:42.607 --> 00:45.697
Or you want to be
a gangster?

00:45.741 --> 00:47.699
We've had our eye
on Desna Simms and Clay Husser

00:47.743 --> 00:49.266
for quite a while now.

00:49.310 --> 00:52.530
You have to promise me immunity
and witness protection.

00:52.574 --> 00:53.531
100%.

00:53.575 --> 00:55.185
So, let's do this.

00:55.229 --> 00:57.709
Hey, Tony.

00:57.753 --> 00:59.755
I'm sorry --[ Gunshot ]

01:02.149 --> 01:04.281
What the hell,
Virginia?!

01:04.325 --> 01:06.892
[ Grunts ]
Ahh!

01:06.936 --> 01:08.720
No one is killing no one.

01:08.764 --> 01:09.765
Do you love me?!

01:09.808 --> 01:10.983
[ Gunshot ]

01:11.027 --> 01:13.203
[ Gunshot ]

01:13.247 --> 01:17.990
♪♪

01:20.776 --> 01:22.386
Dr. Ken: You're lucky.

01:22.430 --> 01:23.779
Looks like the bullet
went clean through.

01:23.822 --> 01:25.563
Oh,
thank Jesus Jim Caviezel.

01:25.607 --> 01:27.913
Bryce: Oh, good, I thought
that was the big one.

01:27.957 --> 01:29.480
I'm serious when I tell you
this is the last thing

01:29.524 --> 01:30.612
I'll do for you.Shh!

01:30.655 --> 01:31.613
I am done with crime
for good.

01:31.656 --> 01:32.918
I get it.
Just hurry up.

01:32.962 --> 01:34.572
Yeah, hurry up.
And remember that --

01:34.616 --> 01:36.270
that's real flesh and
nerve endings in there, okay?

01:36.313 --> 01:37.923
Pol, how you comin'
with that note?

01:37.967 --> 01:38.924
Okay.

01:38.968 --> 01:40.839
Okay.
I think I'm done.

01:40.883 --> 01:43.581
Y'all, this might be
my best forgery yet.

01:43.625 --> 01:46.018
It's complete with spelling
errors and hillbilly-isms.

01:46.062 --> 01:47.759
I-I can't believe
he's dead.

01:47.803 --> 01:50.240
[ As Clay ] "My time yonder
on this here beautiful swamp

01:50.284 --> 01:51.981
is drawing to an end.

01:52.024 --> 01:55.027
It is with deepest regret
that I confess

01:55.071 --> 01:58.335
I done killed the postal worker,
and I can't live with myself

01:58.379 --> 02:02.948
no more on account of my deep
and abiding faith.

02:02.992 --> 02:06.778
My big ol'
Dixie heart's breakin'

02:06.822 --> 02:10.434
that I must bid
you all adieu."

02:10.478 --> 02:12.044
[ Normal voice ]
What y'all think?

02:12.088 --> 02:15.352
I-I-I don't think Clay
would ever use the word "adieu,"

02:15.396 --> 02:17.049
but other than that,
I think it's great.

02:17.093 --> 02:19.269
Now we just gotta get
his fingerprints on that note,

02:19.313 --> 02:21.445
plant the gun,
and call the police hotline.

02:21.489 --> 02:23.621
Jennifer: Shit. Des, you think
this is really gonna work?

02:23.665 --> 02:25.623
I think it'll buy us
some time,

02:25.667 --> 02:27.973
but shit
has definitely changed.

02:28.017 --> 02:30.846
And now I got a assload of work
to do for our escape.

02:30.889 --> 02:33.065
♪ Walk all over you

02:38.245 --> 02:41.291
♪ One o'clock
and on the floor ♪

02:41.335 --> 02:43.467
I'm nervous as a long-tail cat
in a room

02:43.511 --> 02:45.208
full of rocking chairs.Why?

02:45.252 --> 02:47.036
Look,
I know Desna has gone MIA

02:47.079 --> 02:49.212
and told us it's better
we don't know details,

02:49.256 --> 02:51.083
but how is she gonna pay
for it all?

02:51.127 --> 02:52.998
Pol, I thought you had
the money in the bag

02:53.042 --> 02:54.217
'cause the Baron's dead.

02:54.261 --> 02:55.871
No!

02:55.914 --> 02:58.047
His tightwad lawyers
won't release the money to me.

02:58.090 --> 02:59.483
Oh, Lord.

02:59.527 --> 03:01.181
You know what?

03:01.224 --> 03:02.660
Des will find a way.

03:02.704 --> 03:04.358
Her Black ass always does.

03:04.401 --> 03:05.837
Hell, it --
it ain't' the first time

03:05.881 --> 03:09.232
she's been in a shit storm
and gotten out.

03:09.276 --> 03:11.321
Oh. Okay.

03:11.365 --> 03:13.410
You're under arrest
for money laundering and fraud.

03:13.454 --> 03:14.585
I'm what? I'm -- You have the right
to remain silent.

03:14.629 --> 03:15.934
What?

03:15.978 --> 03:17.109
I know
what you're trying to do.

03:19.068 --> 03:21.505
Aah!

03:21.549 --> 03:22.941
Wake your ass up.

03:22.985 --> 03:24.682
Look at this shit.

03:24.726 --> 03:26.902
They left us here
to die.

03:26.945 --> 03:29.339
You know
you just killed a cop.

03:29.383 --> 03:34.214
A dead cop is the least of your
worries right now, Desna Simms.

03:34.257 --> 03:36.216
She does seem to have
nine lives.

03:36.259 --> 03:39.436
This is so depressing.

03:39.480 --> 03:41.133
Just can't believe
y'all are leaving me here.

03:41.177 --> 03:44.528
I mean, I know you don't have
a choice, but still...

03:44.572 --> 03:45.964
Girl, you know it's only
a matter of time

03:46.008 --> 03:47.575
before the feds
come down on your ass.

03:47.618 --> 03:49.141
Why are you not coming
with us?!

03:49.185 --> 03:52.710
Pol, because I can't leave
Brienne and Baylor.

03:52.754 --> 03:54.886
Oh, my God. That one's Brienne,
that one's Baylor.

03:54.930 --> 03:56.061
Yeah, I know!

03:56.105 --> 03:57.237
Listen,
that's not important.

03:57.280 --> 03:59.369
This is
the important part.

03:59.413 --> 04:01.980
I promise I will never turn
on y'all.

04:02.024 --> 04:05.462
How are we supposed to do
this crew without you, though?

04:05.506 --> 04:07.159
I don't know.

04:07.203 --> 04:10.075
When we were good,
we were so good.

04:10.119 --> 04:12.295
♪ I've got
a real good feelin' ♪

04:12.339 --> 04:14.384
♪ That we're doing
something right ♪

04:14.428 --> 04:17.561
♪ When we all get together,
we have the time of our life ♪

04:17.605 --> 04:19.824
Desna: All those years of being
passed over, lowballed,

04:19.868 --> 04:21.739
taken for granted are over.

04:21.783 --> 04:24.307
Y'all are the baddest bitches
in Palmetto.

04:24.351 --> 04:27.397
Together: Br-br-br-br-br-br-ah!

04:27.441 --> 04:36.928
♪♪

04:36.972 --> 04:46.460
♪♪

04:46.503 --> 04:49.114
But let me find out that
I have been replaced

04:49.158 --> 04:50.812
by another white-trash ho.

04:50.855 --> 04:54.119
Oh, you are the only white-trash
ho that I will ever love.

04:54.163 --> 04:57.122
Whenever I see some Velveeta
cheese or some Miracle Whip,

04:57.166 --> 04:58.776
I'm gonna be thinking
about you.

04:58.820 --> 05:00.691
Well, that's the nicest thing
you ever said to me, Pol.

05:00.735 --> 05:02.954
[ Both laugh ]

05:02.998 --> 05:06.958
[ Telephone rings ]

05:07.002 --> 05:08.133
[ Gasps ]

05:08.177 --> 05:09.439
Oh, my gosh!
What?

05:09.483 --> 05:11.789
We are truly blessed...
Pol!

05:11.833 --> 05:13.530
...by St. Julie Andrews!

05:13.574 --> 05:15.837
What?!The Baron's inheritance
came through!

05:15.880 --> 05:17.839
Oh!

05:17.882 --> 05:21.146
Yes! I have access to
his offshore accounts.

05:21.190 --> 05:22.670
Oh, my gosh.

05:22.713 --> 05:24.454
We are setting sail for the life
of leisure, finally.

05:24.498 --> 05:27.457
[ Doorbell rings ]

05:27.501 --> 05:29.503
Hey, Ann, you're here.

05:29.546 --> 05:33.376
We weren't sure you'd come
to enemy territory.

05:33.420 --> 05:34.899
She's not here, right?No, no!

05:34.943 --> 05:36.510
She's down at the docks
doing illegal stuff.

05:36.553 --> 05:38.163
Sounds about right.Okay.

05:38.207 --> 05:40.992
You have to focus
on just one thing --

05:41.036 --> 05:42.820
this little baby.

05:42.864 --> 05:45.475
Let's get
that shitsquib turned.

05:45.519 --> 05:50.480
♪♪

05:50.524 --> 05:53.004
I keep thinking there has to be
some other way.

05:53.048 --> 05:54.266
Well, there ain't.

05:54.310 --> 05:56.660
Happy endings are
for massage parlors.

05:56.704 --> 05:59.184
If Tony was undercover,
we're all in the net.

05:59.228 --> 06:02.013
Besides, sweetie,
you murdered Georgia.

06:02.057 --> 06:03.841
Don't you want to be
free from that?

06:03.885 --> 06:06.191
Yeah, you right.
Yeah.

06:06.235 --> 06:08.498
And more importantly,

06:08.542 --> 06:11.893
does Lilly Pulitzer work
in La Habana?

06:11.936 --> 06:13.547
Isn't that WASPy shit
your thing?

06:13.590 --> 06:15.200
Yeah, but, you know,

06:15.244 --> 06:18.029
I can afford
to switch things up.

06:18.073 --> 06:19.596
Oh.
What are you thinking?

06:19.640 --> 06:25.602
Well, I was thinking about
going very Celia Cruz.

06:25.646 --> 06:28.213
You know, with the
rumba dresses, you know?

06:28.257 --> 06:31.042
And the big frills
and the colors.

06:31.086 --> 06:33.567
Yeah.
Think classic rumbera.

06:33.610 --> 06:36.221
I could do that.[ Laughs ] Come here.

06:36.265 --> 06:38.049
Oh.

06:38.093 --> 06:40.400
Don't you ever stop
appropriatin', Polly-Pol.

06:41.792 --> 06:43.403
[ Laughs ]

06:43.446 --> 06:45.056
iAzúcar!

06:45.100 --> 06:47.232
iAzúcar!

06:47.276 --> 06:49.583
[ Both laugh ]

06:49.626 --> 06:52.412
I was like, "I can't upgrade you
for a fart."

06:52.455 --> 06:54.979
[ Laughs ]
Well, that's what I know.

06:55.023 --> 06:57.547
But when he keeled over
and died,

06:57.591 --> 07:00.289
I gave her 1C
and four hot cookies.

07:00.332 --> 07:01.899
You are so wrong.

07:01.943 --> 07:03.901
Um, give me
about five minutes.

07:03.945 --> 07:06.469
I'll get you under this light,
and then I'll hit them hooves.

07:06.513 --> 07:08.602
Okay.
Alright?

07:10.473 --> 07:11.909
Hi, baby. Hey.

07:11.953 --> 07:14.085
Just came to see how
you're feeling about everything.

07:14.129 --> 07:16.914
Oh, you know, it's like
a broke-down Judy Blume book.

07:16.958 --> 07:19.961
My best friend's leaving town,
and I don't know what to do.

07:22.529 --> 07:24.139
You okay?

07:24.182 --> 07:25.357
You wanna go have a quick one
in the supply closet?

07:25.401 --> 07:26.924
Always...
Yeah.

07:26.968 --> 07:30.537
...but, um, I've been thinking
about Desna's plan.

07:32.974 --> 07:34.628
I think we should go.

07:34.671 --> 07:36.934
To Cuba.

07:36.978 --> 07:38.283
And what about
our children?

07:38.327 --> 07:39.459
We take care of it
when we get there.

07:39.502 --> 07:41.112
I mean,
there's gotta be a way.

07:41.156 --> 07:43.506
And in the meantime, we know
EJ's doing a great job.

07:43.550 --> 07:45.465
Shit sticks, Bryce -- are you
out of your goddamn mind?

07:45.508 --> 07:48.032
I'm not gonna leave my kids
so that I can be a fugitive.

07:48.076 --> 07:49.860
If we don't leave,
the feds are coming for us.

07:49.904 --> 07:51.166
No, they're not.
They're gonna come after Des.

07:51.209 --> 07:52.167
That'll spread to you,
and you know it.

07:52.210 --> 07:53.951
I killed a man.

07:53.995 --> 07:56.127
Well, that's not the first spot
of blood on your hands.

07:56.171 --> 07:58.782
If they are really
building a case -- okay? --

07:58.826 --> 08:02.307
we are on the front page.

08:02.351 --> 08:06.834
The pain clinic, Fentanyl,
Roller, Tony...

08:06.877 --> 08:09.053
I made a list,

08:09.097 --> 08:12.143
and it is long, hon.

08:12.187 --> 08:13.841
You want our kids
to visit us in jail?

08:13.884 --> 08:15.973
Is that what you want?

08:16.017 --> 08:18.323
You know, that would truly be
a Judy Blume book.

08:18.367 --> 08:22.545
"Are You There, God?
It's Me, Brienne and Baylor."

08:22.589 --> 08:24.982
Hmm?
I ain't doing it.

08:25.026 --> 08:27.332
Jenn --I'm not leaving my kids,

08:27.376 --> 08:28.508
end of story.

08:32.381 --> 08:35.471
Oh, the -- the supply
closet's off the table now.

08:42.217 --> 08:44.828
Oh, I can't breathe.

08:44.872 --> 08:47.004
The baby's literally
crushing me.

08:47.048 --> 08:49.398
That is actually
a good sign.

08:49.441 --> 08:50.878
Oh, God, what?

08:50.921 --> 08:53.010
This is a combination
of two methods that --

08:53.054 --> 08:55.099
that are really beneficial
for the fetus.

08:55.143 --> 08:57.537
Additionally, not turning
the baby would require

08:57.580 --> 09:00.017
a Caesarian section,
which is not ideal.

09:00.061 --> 09:03.020
In centuries past, a breech baby
was a death sentence

09:03.064 --> 09:04.369
for a pregnant woman.

09:04.413 --> 09:05.545
Oh, great.

09:05.588 --> 09:09.592
[ Cellphone rings ]

09:09.636 --> 09:12.552
Hello?Jennifer: I know Desna's up
to some top-secret shit.

09:12.595 --> 09:14.205
She's not answering
her phone.

09:14.249 --> 09:15.555
She -- She's not here.

09:15.598 --> 09:17.382
Don't you lie to me,
Dean Simms, okay?

09:17.426 --> 09:18.732
I know
she's probably ashamed

09:18.775 --> 09:20.037
and that's why she don't
want to talk to me.

09:20.081 --> 09:22.213
Uh, Jennifer,
I-I-I don't lie.

09:22.257 --> 09:24.085
It's actually part
of my condition.

09:24.128 --> 09:26.043
I-I find lying immoral.

09:26.087 --> 09:29.438
Well, your immoral sister
is trying to convince my husband

09:29.481 --> 09:30.787
to go with her to Cuba.

09:30.831 --> 09:32.572
I have to admit,
that does sound like her.

09:32.615 --> 09:34.399
She has no boundaries.Yeah.

09:34.443 --> 09:36.401
Well, you tell her that
these are my boundaries

09:36.445 --> 09:38.229
when you see her --
Jenn and Bryce Husser

09:38.273 --> 09:40.623
will not leave
their children.

09:40.667 --> 09:43.713
They will not go to Cuba,
okay?

09:43.757 --> 09:46.498
If we have to get locked up and
just see our kids on visitation,

09:46.542 --> 09:48.283
then that's
what's gonna happen, okay?

09:48.326 --> 09:49.632
That's what we gonna do.

09:49.676 --> 09:51.591
And I look great
in orange.

09:51.634 --> 09:52.722
Do you hear me?

09:52.766 --> 09:54.245
Yes, I hear you.

09:54.289 --> 09:58.119
And I agree --
orange is a great color on you.

10:02.863 --> 10:04.429
[ Line ringing ]Desna: It's Desna. Spill it.

10:04.473 --> 10:05.648
Hey, girl, hey.
I know you're busy right now,

10:05.692 --> 10:07.737
but I just had to tell you.

10:07.781 --> 10:10.087
Remember that time that Jenn
caught Bryce with her mama?

10:10.131 --> 10:11.959
Jennifer: Let's go!

10:12.002 --> 10:15.484
Ahhh!

10:15.527 --> 10:20.750
She was all kinds of pissed
at that lot lizard.

10:20.794 --> 10:22.273
Oh, hell no.

10:22.317 --> 10:23.927
What is this, some kind
of intervention?

10:23.971 --> 10:25.320
Absolutely not.

10:25.363 --> 10:26.974
Wait. Bryce, get out of my way.

10:27.017 --> 10:29.759
Well, then, she got all
wishy-washy and she forgave her.

10:29.803 --> 10:34.285
Mama.[ Crying]

10:34.329 --> 10:36.461
Well, I just talked to her,
and I think

10:36.505 --> 10:38.289
she is gonna
want to come with us.

10:38.333 --> 10:40.030
She just doesn't want to do it
without her kids,

10:40.074 --> 10:43.381
so me and Virginia,
we got a plan...

10:43.425 --> 10:46.471
[ Muffled ] And I can't wait
to tell you about it.

10:46.515 --> 10:48.299
Yeah!

10:48.343 --> 10:50.475
Well, I think
that did the trick.

10:50.519 --> 10:51.694
Yeah?

10:51.738 --> 10:53.565
It better have.

10:53.609 --> 10:57.134
Oh, I haven't been touched by
a man like that in a long time.

10:57.178 --> 10:59.310
Anything to point the fetus
in the right direction.

10:59.354 --> 11:00.703
[ Doorbell rings ]Okay.

11:00.747 --> 11:02.357
Okay.

11:02.400 --> 11:05.490
Oh.

11:05.534 --> 11:06.709
Hey, Jennifer.

11:06.753 --> 11:08.493
Deanie, you best tell me
where she is.

11:08.537 --> 11:09.973
Des-- Desna's not home.

11:10.017 --> 11:11.322
I told you I would give
her your message.

11:11.366 --> 11:12.846
Okay. Well, my patience
is wearing thin.

11:12.889 --> 11:16.719
Hey, Jenn.
Desna screwing you over, too?

11:16.763 --> 11:17.981
Ann, what are you
even doin' here?

11:18.025 --> 11:19.156
Baby shit.

11:19.200 --> 11:20.984
Oh, right.

11:21.028 --> 11:22.594
How is that precious
star nugget?

11:22.638 --> 11:24.031
The head's facing south.

11:24.074 --> 11:26.555
Well, that's how nature
intended it, so...

11:26.598 --> 11:27.991
Are you alright?

11:28.035 --> 11:30.515
'Cause, quite frankly,
you look like crap.

11:30.559 --> 11:32.343
A-And rather pale
and disheveled.

11:32.387 --> 11:35.999
Dean.But very pretty and...

11:36.043 --> 11:37.740
vibrant.I knew I liked you.

11:37.784 --> 11:39.350
Yeah,
I don't know, Ann.

11:39.394 --> 11:41.178
I'm just a little worried
about going to prison.

11:41.222 --> 11:43.354
Which is old hat for you, but
it is virgin territory for me.

11:43.398 --> 11:46.009
Shit is really that bad?Yeah, it could be.

11:46.053 --> 11:47.532
Damn, Jenn.

11:47.576 --> 11:50.231
Well, don't worry
about lockup.

11:50.274 --> 11:51.711
I'm sure you'll be fine.

11:51.754 --> 11:53.190
Really?

11:53.234 --> 11:55.453
No.
Oh.

11:55.497 --> 11:57.194
Dean?
Mm.

11:57.238 --> 11:59.719
Eve?

11:59.762 --> 12:01.111
Shit.

12:01.155 --> 12:02.765
I'm sorry.

12:06.073 --> 12:07.552
Polly: EJ, it's Polly-Pol.

12:07.596 --> 12:09.032
How you doing?

12:09.076 --> 12:11.208
Good, girls are good.
Great.

12:11.252 --> 12:13.776
Listen, I'm gonna get
straight to the point.

12:13.820 --> 12:16.039
Uh, shit has hit the fan,

12:16.083 --> 12:18.607
and we gotta flee
the country A.S.A.P.

12:18.650 --> 12:21.044
Now, you and I both know
that Jenn,

12:21.088 --> 12:22.785
she's not gonna leave
without those kids,

12:22.829 --> 12:25.657
and they need their mama,
so, um, Virginia and I

12:25.701 --> 12:27.747
are just right outside
your house,

12:27.790 --> 12:28.965
and we're wondering
if we could come in

12:29.009 --> 12:31.620
for a little tête-à-tête?

12:31.663 --> 12:34.754
Great.

12:34.797 --> 12:36.756
Virginia, it's go time.

12:39.193 --> 12:41.761
Your lack of helpfulness
is stunning.

12:41.804 --> 12:43.937
Part of being an informant
is to inform.

12:43.980 --> 12:45.416
You want me
to make shit up?

12:45.460 --> 12:47.288
My partner is dead, Ann.

12:47.331 --> 12:50.160
Get with the game, because
if this operation goes bust

