We've got the boys
in blue after us,

27:31.998 --> 27:34.696
and I'm telling you
right now, Ken,

27:34.740 --> 27:36.655
I refuse to go back
to the slammer.

27:36.698 --> 27:37.960
Polly...

27:38.004 --> 27:40.659
So I just...

27:40.702 --> 27:44.140
I need to clear some things
up with you, okay?

27:44.184 --> 27:47.056
I did you dirty, Ken.

27:47.100 --> 27:48.797
Yes, you did, but that --
those are --

27:48.841 --> 27:50.233
those are
some great memories.

27:50.277 --> 27:51.670
No.

27:51.713 --> 27:53.976
I put you through
the wringer.

27:54.020 --> 27:57.501
But the truth is,
I couldn't have made it

27:57.545 --> 28:00.679
through these few years
without you.

28:00.722 --> 28:03.507
And you have no idea
how much you mean to me.

28:03.551 --> 28:05.074
Pol, I'm touched.

28:05.118 --> 28:07.990
So...

28:08.034 --> 28:09.949
This is goodbye, Ken.

28:11.907 --> 28:13.343
A present?

28:13.387 --> 28:14.605
But I didn't get you
anything.

28:14.649 --> 28:15.606
That's okay.

28:15.650 --> 28:17.260
Open it.

28:21.047 --> 28:23.005
You got me a key?
[ Chuckles ]

28:23.049 --> 28:24.833
I mean --
I mean, I love it!

28:24.877 --> 28:27.618
No, Ken, it's a key

28:27.662 --> 28:30.926
to the Kenneth Brickman
Medical Center

28:30.970 --> 28:33.537
in Sarasota.

28:33.581 --> 28:35.191
Wait.
That -- That's my name.

28:35.235 --> 28:36.932
Yeah.
'Cause it's your new practice.

28:36.976 --> 28:38.542
I bought it for you.

28:38.586 --> 28:40.849
And that way, if I'm out
of Palmetto or --

28:40.893 --> 28:42.721
or even the country,

28:42.764 --> 28:45.724
I'll still be a part
of your life.

28:45.767 --> 28:47.856
Are you kidding?
I-I don't know what to say.

28:47.900 --> 28:52.643
You have so much potential,
Ken.

28:52.687 --> 28:55.124
You don't deserve
this life.

28:55.168 --> 28:59.563
I want you to discover who you
really are, by yourself.

28:59.607 --> 29:02.741
Stand on
your own two feet.

29:02.784 --> 29:05.961
Show the world what
Kenneth Brickman can really do.

29:09.095 --> 29:13.055
You know
I will always love you.

29:13.099 --> 29:15.666
Me too, Ken.

29:15.710 --> 29:17.233
Me too.

29:17.277 --> 29:25.111
♪♪

29:25.154 --> 29:27.766
[ Police radio chatter ]

29:27.809 --> 29:29.506
I got the call
about Desna's heroin deal.

29:29.550 --> 29:30.769
She said to meet her in 30.

29:30.812 --> 29:32.422
Game on.
I'm driving.

29:32.466 --> 29:33.772
[ Police radio chatter ]

29:33.815 --> 29:35.338
[ Siren chirps ]

29:35.382 --> 29:37.819
[ Tires squeal ]

29:40.648 --> 29:41.692
Dean.
Yep.

29:41.736 --> 29:43.303
Dean, it's okay.

29:43.346 --> 29:46.262
It's okay.

29:46.306 --> 29:47.829
Okay, come here,
come here.

29:47.873 --> 29:49.962
Put your head here.

29:52.834 --> 29:54.662
Okay,
close your eyes.

29:57.360 --> 30:00.276
You are about to embark
on a restful

30:00.320 --> 30:03.453
and peaceful journey

30:03.497 --> 30:05.499
in which the weight
of the world

30:05.542 --> 30:09.024
and all your troubles
fall away...

30:10.156 --> 30:11.810
[ Siren wails ]

30:11.853 --> 30:13.637
What do you want, Ann?
We're on way to the meet.

30:13.681 --> 30:14.856
Yeah, that's why
I'm calling you.

30:14.900 --> 30:16.466
You're going
to the wrong place.

30:16.510 --> 30:17.946
What? Virginia told me.

30:17.990 --> 30:19.643
The place Desna sent you
is fake.

30:19.687 --> 30:21.341
There's no heroin dealer.

30:21.384 --> 30:22.821
Are you shitting me?

30:22.864 --> 30:24.300
That bitch Desna
played us?

30:24.344 --> 30:27.216
Sure did.
And she's on her way to the dock

30:27.260 --> 30:29.392
to get the hell
out of Palmetto.

30:29.436 --> 30:30.959
Shit.

30:31.003 --> 30:33.396
[ Tires squeal ]

30:33.440 --> 30:35.659
[ Siren wails ]

30:35.703 --> 30:37.574
Why didn't you tell me
as soon as you found out?

30:37.618 --> 30:38.837
I like you, Lori.

30:38.880 --> 30:40.142
I really do.

30:40.186 --> 30:42.753
But I got my own shit
to take care of.

30:44.886 --> 30:46.366
What are you gonna do,
Ann?

30:46.409 --> 30:48.324
As long as that ruthless bitch
is alive,

30:48.368 --> 30:52.328
I'm never gonna be safe
and neither is my baby.

30:52.372 --> 30:54.417
Desna: You sold me out,
didn't you?

30:54.461 --> 31:02.773
♪♪

31:07.604 --> 31:11.347
Eve: No worries, no cares.

31:11.391 --> 31:13.349
Up ahead, you see
an island --

31:13.393 --> 31:15.351
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

31:15.395 --> 31:18.006
This is -- No, this is --
this is not right!

31:18.050 --> 31:19.355
What isn't right?

31:19.399 --> 31:21.096
Desna's in danger.

31:21.140 --> 31:22.619
I-I-I-I can --
I can tell.

31:22.663 --> 31:23.925
I can feel it.

31:23.969 --> 31:25.361
I mean, I can't
actually feel it,

31:25.405 --> 31:26.449
because
that's not possible.

31:26.493 --> 31:28.234
ESP doesn't exist.

31:28.277 --> 31:32.194
But I-I-I can always tell when
something goes wrong with Desna.

31:32.238 --> 31:34.109
What's going wrong?

31:34.153 --> 31:37.025
Whenever she says she has
a plan, it always falls apart.

31:37.069 --> 31:39.201
Her plans suck!
They're terrible.

31:39.245 --> 31:41.377
Actually, they're not actually
thought through, Eve.

31:41.421 --> 31:43.727
And -- And she thinks that
just because she wears

31:43.771 --> 31:46.730
a tight pantsuit that people
can't see her, but I see her.

31:46.774 --> 31:48.950
I see her all the time.
I always see her.

31:48.994 --> 31:50.909
And -- And -- And --
And she's in trouble.

31:50.952 --> 31:52.214
She needs help.
And --

31:52.258 --> 31:53.824
And instead of asking
for any help,

31:53.868 --> 31:55.391
she's gonna try to do
everything by herself,

31:55.435 --> 31:56.958
and then you know what?
People are gonna die.

31:57.002 --> 31:58.568
T-They always do.
People die.

31:58.612 --> 32:00.266
They always die.
They always do.

32:00.309 --> 32:01.963
Maybe they won't this time.
Maybe --

32:02.007 --> 32:03.486
Eve, you're not --
you're not listening to me!

32:03.530 --> 32:07.795
They always -- mmm.

32:07.838 --> 32:09.231
I-I-I've had
to save her before.

32:09.275 --> 32:10.493
I -- I have to go
save her.

32:10.537 --> 32:12.408
Wait. Wait.
Dean, wait!

32:12.452 --> 32:13.844
You're not going anywhere.

32:18.458 --> 32:19.763
You betrayed me.

32:19.807 --> 32:21.983
Stings, doesn't it?

32:22.027 --> 32:24.638
I sure as shit ain't going
down with you.

32:27.989 --> 32:29.860
You would shoot
a pregnant woman?

32:29.904 --> 32:31.427
[ Siren wails ]

32:31.471 --> 32:34.256
I don't know
why I'm surprised.

32:34.300 --> 32:35.779
Never doubt this queen.

32:35.823 --> 32:36.955
Or this one.

32:36.998 --> 32:38.260
[ Gunshot ]

32:38.304 --> 32:39.653
[ Siren wails ]

32:39.696 --> 32:45.311
[ Gunshots ]

32:45.354 --> 32:46.486
Shit!

32:46.529 --> 32:47.487
Hurry the hell up
to the docks.

32:47.530 --> 32:50.969
We need them both alive.

32:51.012 --> 32:52.144
I can't let you go.

32:52.187 --> 32:53.623
It's --
It's not your choice.

32:53.667 --> 32:55.147
I'm a grown man.

32:55.190 --> 32:56.626
I'm gonna find Desna.Why do you think I'm here?

32:56.670 --> 32:58.280
Desna knew you were gonna
try to do this.

32:58.324 --> 33:00.108
She -- She sent you?See, honey?

33:00.152 --> 33:02.284
She does have a plan.God!

33:02.328 --> 33:05.287
Even when she's skipping town,
she's so controlling!

33:05.331 --> 33:06.985
Okay.
Where is she, Dr. Ken?

33:07.028 --> 33:08.377
She asked me to look after you,
Dean.

33:08.421 --> 33:09.726
You don't need her.

33:09.770 --> 33:10.989
You don't need to save her,
either.

33:11.032 --> 33:12.468
Yes, I do.
She can't do this alone!

33:12.512 --> 33:14.470
I have to --She has to do it alone.

33:14.514 --> 33:16.211
She has to.

33:16.255 --> 33:19.649
And if you're really
a grown man,

33:19.693 --> 33:23.305
then you have to let go.

33:23.349 --> 33:24.393
But she needs me.

33:24.437 --> 33:26.308
Does she?

33:26.352 --> 33:29.094
Or are you just scared
of being without her?

33:31.183 --> 33:33.315
Sometimes we have to let go
of the people we love

33:33.359 --> 33:36.840
because it's
the right thing to do.

33:36.884 --> 33:38.538
I want to run
after Polly --

33:38.581 --> 33:42.368
I can't imagine my life
without her.

33:42.411 --> 33:45.153
But I have to.

33:45.197 --> 33:46.850
For both our sakes.

33:46.894 --> 33:49.940
♪♪

33:49.984 --> 33:52.030
[ Gunshots ]

33:52.073 --> 33:54.423
[ Siren wailing ]

33:54.467 --> 34:01.865
♪♪

34:01.909 --> 34:03.432
[ Gasps ]

34:03.476 --> 34:10.874
♪♪

34:10.918 --> 34:18.360
♪♪

34:18.404 --> 34:20.101
[ Gunshot ]

34:20.145 --> 34:22.277
♪♪

34:22.321 --> 34:23.626
[ Grunts ]

34:23.670 --> 34:25.063
Shit!

34:25.106 --> 34:31.069
♪♪

34:31.112 --> 34:32.679
[ Gunshot ]

34:34.333 --> 34:35.377
Desna...

34:35.421 --> 34:38.815
Say hi
to Arlene for me.

34:38.859 --> 34:40.730
Bitch.

34:40.774 --> 34:43.081
[ Gunshot ]

34:43.124 --> 34:45.126
Come on, come on.
I got you.

34:45.170 --> 34:47.563
Go, go, go, go, go!Go, go, go!

34:47.607 --> 34:50.262
Where the hell
are they going?

34:51.872 --> 34:55.571
♪ And you keep thinkin'
that you'll never get burnt ♪

34:55.615 --> 34:56.572
[ Sirens wailing ]

34:56.616 --> 34:57.834
♪ Ha!

34:57.878 --> 34:59.097
Come on!

34:59.140 --> 35:00.272
Move your asses!

35:00.315 --> 35:02.578
Go, go, go!

35:02.622 --> 35:04.276
Stop right there!
You're all under arrest!

35:04.319 --> 35:09.107
♪ And what he knows you ain't
had time to learn ♪

35:09.150 --> 35:12.240
♪ These boots are made
for walkin' ♪

35:12.284 --> 35:15.287
♪ And that's just
what they'll do ♪

35:15.330 --> 35:20.422
♪ One of these days these boots
are gonna walk all over you ♪

35:20.466 --> 35:24.600
♪♪

35:24.644 --> 35:26.602
Lori: Get the Coast Guard!

35:26.646 --> 35:28.300
♪ Are you ready, boots?

35:30.476 --> 35:32.478
♪ Start walkin' Shit!

35:32.521 --> 35:39.224
♪♪

35:43.358 --> 35:52.498
♪♪

35:52.541 --> 36:01.681
♪♪

36:01.724 --> 36:10.907
♪♪

36:10.951 --> 36:20.090
♪♪

36:20.134 --> 36:29.230
♪♪

36:29.274 --> 36:33.234
♪♪

36:33.278 --> 36:35.454
[ Doorbell rings ]

36:38.457 --> 36:40.023
Hi!

36:40.067 --> 36:41.895
Welcome back!Look at this dude.

36:41.938 --> 36:43.418
It's daddy!What's going on?

36:43.462 --> 36:45.855
What's going -- Oh, what?
What have you done?

36:45.899 --> 36:47.335
This is amazing.

36:47.379 --> 36:49.511
Eve: Yeah,
we made some changes.

36:49.555 --> 36:51.557
I like it.[ Chuckles ]

36:51.600 --> 36:52.775
So, how was your trip?

36:52.819 --> 36:55.517
Oh. Ah-maz-ing!

36:55.561 --> 36:56.910
I had so much fun in Vegas.

36:56.953 --> 36:59.042
I-I-I really needed
to clear my head.

36:59.086 --> 37:00.218
Here, here.

37:00.261 --> 37:02.568
I, uh, brought you
a souvenir.

37:02.611 --> 37:04.744
Now don't be offended.

37:06.136 --> 37:08.574
[ Laughs ]

37:08.617 --> 37:09.879
How can I be offended?

37:09.923 --> 37:11.794
It is true. [ Laughs ]

37:11.838 --> 37:13.709
Thank you.
Sure.

37:13.753 --> 37:15.972
So what'd you do?

37:16.016 --> 37:17.539
Oh.
So many terrifying things.

37:17.583 --> 37:19.237
The Stratosphere
roller coaster,

37:19.280 --> 37:21.151
the Grand Canyon
helicopter tour,

37:21.195 --> 37:22.892
sky diving,
and you know what?

37:22.936 --> 37:25.939
Dr. Kenneth Brickman not
only survived but thrived.

37:25.982 --> 37:27.810
So happy for you.

37:27.854 --> 37:29.290
Your baby missed you.

37:29.334 --> 37:30.987
Oh,
and I missed him, too.

37:31.031 --> 37:32.902
But not with the desperate
abandonment I was afraid of.

37:32.946 --> 37:34.295
Uh, don't tell him that.

37:34.339 --> 37:36.558
Your secret's safe with me.
[ Chuckles ]

37:36.602 --> 37:39.561
Hey, Dean, honey,
come down here!

37:39.605 --> 37:41.259
How is he?

37:41.302 --> 37:42.564
Ah, same.

37:42.608 --> 37:44.131
Yeah.

37:44.174 --> 37:47.395
I mean, Desna was
his entire life before you.

37:47.439 --> 37:51.312
We're taking it moment
by moment.

37:51.356 --> 37:53.183
Hi, honey,
look who's here.

37:53.227 --> 37:57.100
Hey, Dean.Glad tidings and felicitations.

37:57.144 --> 37:58.319
Oh, I brought you this...

37:58.363 --> 37:59.625
Yeah.

37:59.668 --> 38:01.627
Ready?

38:01.670 --> 38:04.760
Psh-ah!

38:04.804 --> 38:07.459
Mm.
That's funny.

38:07.502 --> 38:09.852
Here.

38:09.896 --> 38:13.116
Oh,
and I almost forgot.

38:13.160 --> 38:15.510
This was outside
your door.

38:15.554 --> 38:17.120
It doesn't say
who it's from.

38:17.164 --> 38:24.867
♪♪

38:24.911 --> 38:34.094
♪♪

38:45.192 --> 38:48.151
[ "On the Wings of Love" plays]

38:48.195 --> 38:49.631
Desna: Hi, Deanie.

38:49.675 --> 38:51.851
I know you've probably
been upset.

38:51.894 --> 38:54.027
I have missed you so much

38:54.070 --> 38:57.160
and wanted to tell you
what happened.

38:57.204 --> 38:58.379
Hi -- Hi, Des.

38:58.423 --> 39:00.207
And I wish --
Stop it!

39:00.250 --> 39:03.384
Everyone thought that me
and Ann were mortal enemies

39:03.428 --> 39:05.821
after that big blowout
at the salon.

39:05.865 --> 39:08.824
A-And it was true
for a real long time.

39:08.868 --> 39:12.480
Tell me what it's gonna take to
get you the hell outta my life.

39:12.524 --> 39:13.916
Ann.

39:13.960 --> 39:15.527
Ann, please!

39:19.095 --> 39:21.359
After we almost lost Jenn,

39:21.402 --> 39:25.014
Ann and I were able to get
to a deeper place.

39:25.058 --> 39:26.407
You stalking me now?

39:26.451 --> 39:28.714
I can't let you
just walk away.

39:30.890 --> 39:32.718
I finally fell on the sword

39:32.761 --> 39:35.111
and apologized to her,
for real.

39:35.155 --> 39:39.028
And we figured out a way
we could fool the DEA together.

39:39.072 --> 39:42.510
So we set a plan in motion
that was pretty damn risky,

39:42.554 --> 39:44.860
with Ann becoming
an informant.

39:44.904 --> 39:48.037
If I tell you everything I know
about Desna and Clay,

39:48.081 --> 39:52.433
you have to promise me immunity
and witness protection.

39:52.477 --> 39:54.522
100%.

39:54.566 --> 39:56.872
The most important thing
we had to do

39:56.916 --> 40:00.223
was to keep up this act
of being mortal enemies.

40:00.267 --> 40:04.445
So Ann called her DEA handler
to witness her death.

40:04.489 --> 40:06.055
Desna...

40:06.099 --> 40:08.710
[ Gunshot ]

40:08.754 --> 40:11.713
Polly gave me some leads,
and I spent the last few days

40:11.757 --> 40:15.543
putting together a dream team
of ex-Navy SEALs,

40:15.587 --> 40:16.979
special effects dudes,

40:17.023 --> 40:19.939
even a tech crew
from a Vegas magic act

40:19.982 --> 40:22.245
who happened to be
between gigs.

40:22.289 --> 40:23.464
Come on!

40:23.508 --> 40:25.727
Move your asses!

40:25.771 --> 40:27.468
She's looking --
She's watching us!

40:27.512 --> 40:30.428
To the feds, it looked like
we were trying to escape

40:30.471 --> 40:32.604
on a boat, which we were.

40:32.647 --> 40:36.085
But, Deanie, it wasn't
the one that exploded.

40:36.129 --> 40:39.437
The bomb was tossed
into an identical boat

40:39.480 --> 40:41.830
that was hidden in the cove.

40:41.874 --> 40:43.745
While that boat sped away,

40:43.789 --> 40:47.923
a team disguised our boat
while we hid out of sight.

40:47.967 --> 40:50.796
What the feds saw
was a decoy boat...

40:50.839 --> 40:52.798
♪♪

40:52.841 --> 40:55.583
Ah![ Officers gasp ]

40:55.627 --> 40:57.455
...while we all sailed off

40:57.498 --> 41:00.022
into the most
bomb-ass sunset...

41:00.066 --> 41:02.764
♪ On the wings of love♪

41:02.808 --> 41:05.288
Desna: I love you, Deanie,
and I'm so sorry

41:05.332 --> 41:07.290
I let you think I was gone.

41:07.334 --> 41:08.988
One of these days, though,
baby,

41:09.031 --> 41:13.383
I'm gonna see you
and that little baby of yours.

41:13.427 --> 41:14.863
Yeah.

41:14.907 --> 41:17.779
Okay, Des.

41:17.823 --> 41:18.780
That's --

41:18.824 --> 41:21.783
Honey, are you alright?

41:21.827 --> 41:24.307
Yeah, I-I'm good.

41:24.351 --> 41:26.309
I-I-I'll be right down.

41:26.353 --> 41:33.360
♪♪

41:35.841 --> 41:38.539
♪♪

41:38.583 --> 41:41.411
[ Man singing in Spanish ]

41:41.455 --> 41:48.636
♪♪

41:48.680 --> 41:50.986
[ Laughter ]

41:51.030 --> 41:54.207
♪♪

41:54.250 --> 41:56.252
Polly: [ Sighs ]

41:56.296 --> 41:57.993
Shut up.

41:58.037 --> 42:01.040
Okay.
I love you, too, Roller.

42:01.083 --> 42:02.171
Mwah!

42:02.215 --> 42:03.477
I'll see you later.

42:06.088 --> 42:08.526
"I love you, too, Roller.
I'll see you later."

42:08.569 --> 42:10.658
[ Laughter ]

42:10.702 --> 42:12.181
Shut up!

42:12.225 --> 42:15.010
Y'all, it's --
it's been a whole two months.

42:15.054 --> 42:16.577
-Yeah.
-Two months.

42:16.621 --> 42:18.187
I feel like
we in the clear.Oh, yeah.

42:18.231 --> 42:20.581
And Roller's back sweatin'
out your edges, girl.

42:20.625 --> 42:23.062
-Hey!
-I know that's right.

42:23.105 --> 42:24.716
That's why I had
to lay them down.

42:24.759 --> 42:26.674
No, he laid you down.

42:26.718 --> 42:29.198
[ Laughter ]

42:29.242 --> 42:31.853
But it just seems like,
when I think about it,

42:31.897 --> 42:36.205
all that mess in Palmetto
was a lifetime ago.

42:36.249 --> 42:39.557
It's not my first time,
but ain't it fun being dead?

42:39.600 --> 42:41.559
[ Laughter ]

42:41.602 --> 42:43.604
Sweetheart, where's
the margarita mix?

42:43.648 --> 42:45.214
Jennifer: Baby, I don't know.

42:45.258 --> 42:46.781
You're just gonna have to
find it your damn self.

42:46.825 --> 42:48.870
And when you find it,
can you make me a virgin?

42:48.914 --> 42:51.743
Sorry, babe, I believe that
ship has already sailed.

42:51.786 --> 42:52.918
[ Whooping, laughter ]

42:52.961 --> 42:54.397
Do not encourage him.

42:54.441 --> 42:55.964
Do not.

42:56.008 --> 43:00.055
But seriously, y'all, like,
think about all the shit

43:00.099 --> 43:01.404
we been through.

